This paper deals with resource allocation and pricing in IoT networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves optimization techniques and game theory, which are subfields of theoretical computer science (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of a multi-objective optimization problem, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY) and computational engineering (cs.CE).
